<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<!-- ====================================================================== 
   El calentamiento es un <exploration> (distinto a las otras actividades)
   Para RRRRR usar el estilo del calentamiento. Por ejemplo, usar 
   RRRRRR=observa con los "Observa y Pregúntate"
===========================================================================  -->
<exploration xml:id="warm-verdaderoFalso-fraccionesUnitarias" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Verdadero o falso: Fracciones unitaria</title>

<statement>
  <p>Decide si cada afirmación es verdadera o falsa. Prepárate para explicar tu razonamiento.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><p><m>\frac{1}{2} \gt \frac{1}{4}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\frac{1}{4} \gt \frac{1}{3}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\frac{1}{6} \gt \frac{1}{8}</m></p></li>
  </ul>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>True: I know that one fourth is half the size of one half.</li>
      <li>False: If the whole is split in 3 parts, those parts are bigger than if there were 4 parts, so one fourth is smaller than one third.</li>
      <li>True: Eighths are smaller than sixths because if we split the whole into more parts, each part is smaller.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-NF-A-3-d" text="custom">3.NF.A.3.d</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this True or False is to elicit insights students have about comparing unit fractions. The reasoning students do helps to deepen their understanding of what the denominator of a fraction means. It will also be helpful later when students compare fractions with the same numerator.</p>
    <p>In this activity, students have an opportunity to look for and make use of structure (MP7) because they notice that a larger denominator indicates that a whole is split into more parts. The more parts the whole is split into, the smaller those parts will be.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Display one statement.</li>
      <li>
        <q>Hagan una señal cuando sepan si la afirmación es verdadera o no, y puedan explicar cómo lo saben</q>
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: quiet think time</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Share and record answers and strategy.</li>
      <li>Repeat with each statement.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Consider asking:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><q>¿Alguien puede expresar el razonamiento de <fillin/> de otra forma?</q></li>
          <li><q>¿Alguien quiere agregar algo al razonamiento de <fillin/>?</q></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</exploration>